Class SchemaJJv1

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.apptik.json.wrapper.JsonElementWrapper<io.apptik.json.JsonObject>
      • io.apptik.json.wrapper.JsonObjectWrapper
        • io.apptik.json.schema.Schema
          • io.apptik.json.schema.SchemaV4
            • io.apptik.json.schema.SchemaJJv1
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    io.apptik.json.ElementWrapper, io.apptik.json.wrapper.MetaInfo, java.io.Serializable

    public class SchemaJJv1
extends SchemaV4
    ABSOLUTELY EXPERIMENTAL New keyword is "extends" which is used as "merge" (v5 proposal) but with easier syntax. es: { "merge": { "source": { "type": "object", "properties": { "p": { "type": "string" } }, "additionalProperties": false }, "with": { "properties": { "q": { "enum": [ null ] } } } } } equals to { "extends": { "type": "object", "properties": { "p": { "type": "string" } }, "additionalProperties": false }, "properties": { "q": { "enum": [ null ] } } } This is really powerful when used with $ref "equivalent keyword is used here to provide list of links to equivalent schemas/rdf classes"
    See Also:
